{"id":12572,"date":"2023-01-16T20:05:33","date_gmt":"2023-01-16T20:05:33","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/?p=12572"},"modified":"2023-01-16T20:05:37","modified_gmt":"2023-01-16T20:05:37","slug":"scapegoating-unhoused-and-mentally-ill-people","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/scapegoating-unhoused-and-mentally-ill-people\/","title":{"rendered":"Scapegoating Unhoused and &#8220;Mentally Ill&#8221; People\u00a0"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"12573\" data-permalink=\"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/scapegoating-unhoused-and-mentally-ill-people\/screenshot-mayor-adams-order-severe-mental-illness\/\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/screenshot-mayor-adams-order-severe-mental-illness-scaled.jpg?fit=2560%2C1598&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"2560,1598\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"screenshot-mayor-adams-order-severe-mental-illness\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/screenshot-mayor-adams-order-severe-mental-illness-scaled.jpg?fit=300%2C187&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/screenshot-mayor-adams-order-severe-mental-illness-scaled.jpg?fit=800%2C499&amp;ssl=1\" fetchpriority=\"high\" width=\"800\" height=\"499\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/screenshot-mayor-adams-order-severe-mental-illness.jpg?resize=800%2C499&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"Screenshot of website of the NYC Office of the Mayor with photo showing Mayor Adams making an announcement with several people behind him and a headline that reads &quot;Mayor Adams Announces Plan to Provide Care for Individuals Suffering From Untreated Severe Mental Illness Across NYC.&quot;\" class=\"wp-image-12573\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/screenshot-mayor-adams-order-severe-mental-illness-scaled.jpg?resize=1024%2C639&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/screenshot-mayor-adams-order-severe-mental-illness-scaled.jpg?resize=300%2C187&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/screenshot-mayor-adams-order-severe-mental-illness-scaled.jpg?resize=768%2C479&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/screenshot-mayor-adams-order-severe-mental-illness-scaled.jpg?resize=1536%2C959&amp;ssl=1 1536w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/screenshot-mayor-adams-order-severe-mental-illness-scaled.jpg?resize=2048%2C1278&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/screenshot-mayor-adams-order-severe-mental-illness-scaled.jpg?w=1600&amp;ssl=1 1600w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/screenshot-mayor-adams-order-severe-mental-illness-scaled.jpg?w=2400&amp;ssl=1 2400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p>Former police captain Eric Adams won the 2021 New York City mayoral election, in year two of the pandemic, with a &#8220;war on crime&#8221; campaign that has often manifested as a war on unhoused and mentally disabled people. Unhoused people had been forced into parks and streets as a result of subway closures for overnight disinfection, leading to popular anxieties about increased homelessness (with actual numbers difficult to measure). As MTA ridership rebounded, fears regarding &#8220;transit crime,&#8221; including a few high-profile incidents of violence by mentally disabled people, led Adams to announce large-scale police patrols of the subway system shortly after he was sworn in on January 1, 2022. On November 29, Adams additionally <a href=\"https:\/\/www.nyc.gov\/office-of-the-mayor\/news\/870-22\/mayor-adams-plan-provide-care-individuals-suffering-untreated-severe-mental#\/0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">announced an 11-point agenda<\/a> that would allow unhoused and\/or mentally disabled people to be involuntarily hospitalized, with NYPD and DOH &#8220;co-response teams&#8221; deployed in subways to remove &#8220;those appearing to have serious mental health issues.&#8221; Outcry from disability activists pointed to a lack of hospital space as well as economic and social supports and, more importantly, to the civil rights platform of the global deinstitutionalization movement since the 1960s. \u2014Mara Mills<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Watch Mayor Adams&#8217;s announcement below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed aligncenter is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"Mayor Eric Adams Delivers Address on Mental Health Crisis in New York City\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/2OVMFqc7tGI?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n","protected":false},"exc